reviews.text: They Lie to me NO Vegan Option & Waiting  There for Nothing waste of time at the Table. I Did NOT Like What Was on The Menu & it was Disgusting. So I left quick. I Did not want to be Seen There Either. Because I'm kinda famous. Definitely Not My Type Of Place.

I am vegan and one of my friends who went with me eats halal (my friend enjoyed the lamb). We loved the food and the experience so much that we came back the next night also. The staff and owners are very nice. Next time I am back in Albuquerque I will eat here again.

My favorite Indian food lunch buffet here in Albuquerque.  We make it a point to go meet at least once a month with our friends.  They have all the great stuff you'd expect at a Indian food buffet and they do a great job at all of it.  It's typically bustling and busy at lunch, but with several dining areas and attentive polite staff that are constantly on top of everything, it's always a pleasurable experience.

First time coming here, and first time eating Indian food, and I have to say that I loved it! The location is pretty old and might be in need for an update, but they make up for it with the great food. I went for lunch, and they have their buffet, which makes it really easy to get a sample of their offerings
Always wonderful!  Have been a patron for years, and it's always a good bet.  Had the baked eggplant and lamb meatballs.....great!  Always have an appetizer.

Graeat luscious garden with many, many bungalows. Very good breakfast-  western and asian. Good coffee, smoking is otside but there are also good seatings. Motorbike and car rent from the resort. Beautiful and clean pool. Room service- 8 of 10 but decent. Room service with food ordering. Good food. Tasted only local though. Public toilets- 7 of 10. Nice and quiet resort to stay in this busy town. 7 eleven is just few hundred meters around the corner if needed.

Gardens were absolutely lovely, rooms great and beds nice. Pool was good. Only issue was the noise from neighbouring rooms... could hear everything in adjoining rooms. They were doing some rennovation so hopefully an issue being addressed.

Room was great, renovated recently and had one of those rainfall showers. Very clean. I ordered a Thai foot massage and a glass of wine at the end of the night, it was EVERYTHING! Hotel staff is very friendly, service is superb - I will definitely be coming back next time I’m in Chiang Rai.

The pool villas have paper wall's and can hear every single word from the room next door. The room maids start working at 7am and talking and laughing super loud that sleeping impossible. The massage chair in the lobby offer the service for 10THB but only eat money and not work and if ask the concierge on the counter he answer: not my business???
And even know it's broken still let it run to cheat next guest???
All in one it's for the price the most worth Hotel I ever was here in Chiang Rai.
Will sure never meet again!!!!
Lacking atmosphere despite lovely gardens.  Feels a bit like a retirement village; staff lacking in customer service skills.

Amazing food, the wait is always wrong and servers will always be rushing. Not the best service but for a college student neighborhood it's pretty decent. The Bread and the Omelate was amazing, the biscuit needed the jelly but the Home fries was a great add on. Decent price for the size, more paying for the looks. Food looks exactly like the pictures.

I requested a two-top on the bench (that had previously been a two-top; I watched the previous couple leave and the table get cleaned). I was told by the host to basically shrug off/he was managing his tables, and that, as a caveat, he might ask us to "move" if a 6 top came in. I'm sorry but, excuse me? No. I've worked in restaurants on and off for 15 years and never once said something like that to someone. The tables are so close to each other that you feel like your shoulders are about to graze the people next to you; consider removing even just one two-top and everyone - your customers and your staff - will be a lot more relaxed. What we ordered was bland/under-salted and/or weirdly-seasoned (way too much nutmeg in the biscuits and gravy), and we left paying $50 for an offensive and underwhelming experience.
Food was really tasty. Being a vegan, I always wonder about restaurants and how they address my needs but this one nailed it.
This place is always busy for a reason . They do an excellent job at working the very small space they have. Amazing food and they make their own biscuits.  A true Farm house style breakfast.
The best place to eat breakfast in Berkeley. I love it.

This is a great place to have a celebration, gatherings or meetings. This place is wonderful. You can sit indoors or outdoors overlooking the marina on a warm sunset night. Great atmosphere! Great service... Sunday champagne brunch was amazing. Great variety of food and good selection on the menu. The management staff caters to your needs. Vallet parking is $5.00. I love this place.

We ate simple here with a club sandwich and a kids quesadilla. Both were well prepared and served quickly. 

Their patio seating in back has a marina view but no foot traffic by the tables. In front they have a coy pond with some hungry fish.

I go salsa dancing here and they're really great! Very fun and active, nice atmosphere. Havent tried the food as I go for more social dance experience but seems like a great place to eat both for friends and romantic scene. Glad they are still around.

Very attentive waiting staff was refilling drinks before being asked. Parking was valet only since I believe they were painting the parking spot numbers at the time. I had the roast beef dip sandwich and garlic mashed potatoes which was very tasty.

The restaurant is 3.5 stars for food & service, ambience is 5 stars for sure. 

OTOH, the bar on this Saturday night was off the charts for live music with the Rick Whitfield Band. Even the First Lady of Folk, Joni Mitchell, was in the house and the band played Woodstock in tribute. Very cool!
